reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great For the Price!
reviews.reviewText: If you are building on a budget this is a great option, the RGB is static which I don't mind as the PC it went into had a rainbow RGB theme already. I installed this cooler on my buddies i7-4790k and it keeps it more than cool enough even with a decent overclock, and it leaps and bounds better than the intel stock cooler that had 10 year old thermal paste on it. Did I mention this cooler comes with new thermal paste? Amazing for the $18 I paid and it even had next day shipping!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars ARGB? False - STATIC RGB is it
reviews.reviewText: This is labeled as ARGB but the fan doesn’t even have a argb cable to plug into your motherboard, only the pwm cpu fan. Went to go into the product’s description more and it says that this is Rgb static.If you want a cpu cooler to be delivered the same day, you are basically stuck with thermaltake as an option. Horrible false advertisement. This isn’t the way to go about to sell products. I had to buy a version that does allow for motherboard sync.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Nice for systems that don't have ARGB headers

reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Not ARGB as described
reviews.reviewText: The fan is a static rainbow color and not addressable as described in the description. It would have got 5 stars if it wasn't false description. Other than that it performs really well. Keeps an AMD 5700x around 35c idle, 60c during gaming. It was very simple to install.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars It’s Nice but there’s a downside.
reviews.reviewText: The quality is good, the installation is nice and easy, i upgraded from a AMD cooler and it keeps my ryzen 5 5600g at no higher that n 50c.i just wish the fan came with a ARGB cable. It’s a solid color the fan although you can put another fan and probably daisy chain it. the installation is good, so is the quality just wished it was actually ARGB

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Choice for CPU Cooling
reviews.reviewText: It's big, quiet and it keeps my Ryzen 7 nice and cool! The fan is quiet and looks fantastic, too. The only drawback was that my DIMMs prevented me from mounting the cooler horizontally. If the cooler were a bit taller, or my DIMMs a little shorter...but I just had to have those damned RGB DIMMs.
